    <item>
      <title>Cellular Automata and Models of Artificial Life</title>
      <link>https://barahudcova.com/teaching/life/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://barahudcova.com/teaching/life/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;official website of the course: &lt;a href=&#34;https://edu.epfl.ch/coursebook/en/cellular-automata-and-models-of-artificial-life-MATH-527&#34;&gt;https://edu.epfl.ch/coursebook/en/cellular-automata-and-models-of-artificial-life-MATH-527&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Course Materials&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am currently in the process of writing lecture notes for the course and I will progressively update them here. Since this is the first draft, if you spot any mistake or have any remarks, I would greatly appreciate if you let me know.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap1.pdf&#34;&gt;Lecture Notes Chapter 1: Self-Reference in Programs&lt;/a&gt; &lt;em&gt;last updated: 3.3.2026&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap2.pdf&#34;&gt;Lecture Notes Chapter 2: The Logic of Self-Replication&lt;/a&gt; &lt;em&gt;last updated: 19.3.2026&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap3.pdf&#34;&gt;Lecture Notes Chapter 3: Beyond Exact Self-Replication&lt;/a&gt; &lt;em&gt;last updated: 26.3.2026&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap4.pdf&#34;&gt;Lecture Notes Chapter 4: A First Look at the Space of Cellular Automata&lt;/a&gt; &lt;em&gt;last updated: 2.4.2026&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lectures&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lecture 1: Introduction to the course, Turing machines, Computability.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8V9-ZNqwqXs&amp;amp;t=1s&#34;&gt;Part 1 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XvZkgY0p8V4&#34;&gt;Part 2 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, we covered pages 1&amp;ndash;4 from the &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap1.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 1&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lecture 2: Universal Turing machines, Undecidability.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HgmJIVjeAt0&#34;&gt;Part 1 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MZHcApyOFlc&#34;&gt;Part 2 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, we covered pages 5&amp;ndash;9 from the &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap1.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 1&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lecture 3: Quines, Kleene&amp;rsquo;s Recursion Theorems.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-Bghss4y9ZY&amp;amp;t=1368s&#34;&gt;Part 1 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5aP77ji70PE&amp;amp;t=868s&#34;&gt;Part 2 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, we covered pages 9&amp;ndash;15 from the &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap1.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 1&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lecture 4: Von Neumann&amp;rsquo;s kinematic model, and CA self-replicator.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vm8CW7Gjke0&amp;amp;t=4s&#34;&gt;Part 1 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DvpgPdwK6CI&#34;&gt;Part 2 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, we covered pages 1&amp;ndash;10 from &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap2.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lecture 5: Von Neumann&amp;rsquo;s CA self-replicator and Broader Vision.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BW9zfBqGOyU&#34;&gt;Part 1 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2k8NZdDgEQc&#34;&gt;Part 2 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, we covered pages 11&amp;ndash;20 from &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap2.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 2&lt;/a&gt;, and pages 1&amp;ndash;2 from &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap3.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lecture 6: Beyond Exact Self-Replication.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1EaJIcnNvCw&amp;amp;t=6s&#34;&gt;Part 1 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kNbMGB4f0wI&#34;&gt;Part 2 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, we covered pages 2&amp;ndash;16 from &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap3.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 3&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lecture 7: A First Look at the Space of Cellular Automata.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UNGulo06Q40&amp;amp;t=1s&#34;&gt;Part 1 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YjpZzEpDZEk&#34;&gt;Part 2 Recording&lt;/a&gt;, we covered the whole &lt;a href=&#34;./lecture_notes/lecture_notes_chap4.pdf&#34;&gt;chapter 4&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Worksheets&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./worksheets/ex1.pdf&#34;&gt;Worksheet 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./worksheets/ex2.pdf&#34;&gt;Worksheet 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./worksheets/ex3.pdf&#34;&gt;Worksheet 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./worksheets/ex4.pdf&#34;&gt;Worksheet 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./worksheets/ex5.pdf&#34;&gt;Worksheet 5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./worksheets/ex6.pdf&#34;&gt;Worksheet 6&lt;/a&gt; &lt;em&gt;last updated: 30.3.2026&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;./worksheets/ex7.pdf&#34;&gt;Worksheet 7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Software Tools&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://golly.sourceforge.io/&#34;&gt;Golly&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/frotaur/PyCA&#34;&gt;PyCA github&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mI_hMSUCvAE&#34;&gt;PyCA demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://barahudcova.com/teaching/life/teaser/&#34;&gt;Course Teaser: What is Artificial Life About?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
